        This method returns an integer specifying the size of the invoking array. An empty array has size 0 (zero).

        This method appends x to the invoking array.

      • add

        void add(int more,
       IloIntExpr x)
        This method appends x to the invoking array multiple times. The argument more specifies how many times.

      • add

        void add(IloIntExprArray ax)
        This method appends the elements in ax to the invoking array.

      • remove

        void remove(int first,
          int nb)
        This method removes elements from the invoking array. It begins removing elements at the index specified by first, and it removes nb elements (nb = 1 by default).

      • clear

        void clear()
        This method removes all the elements from the invoking array. In other words, it produces an empty array.
